	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hello my fellow Erudites,<BR>
<BR>
I, like many of you, quickly tired of Toxx and so first went to Freeport.  My faction was decent, but I couldn't get any experience in the commonlands because a) everything either conned green or red, no inbetween, especially once I hit my 6th season, and b) everyone who wanted to group was looking for tanks or healers, and as a magician I was often forced to solo.  I know many of you had good experiences is Freeport, but it didn't work for me.<BR>
<BR>
So I managed to find my way to Qeynos (do not make the journey from Freeport to Qeynos on foot as a newbie, especially at night--you will die).  The Qeynos hills and other nearby hunting grounds are great--I'm very close to my 8th season and looking forward to visiting the gnoll camps when I get my new spells and pet.<BR>
<BR>
But the important matter that no one here has talked about (that I've seen) is how I can raise my faction with the Order of the Three, the spellcasters of Qeynos.  I've raised faction with nearly everyone else, but I can't train, buy spells, or even do certain quests in Qeynos because the Order of the Three seem to be a bit hostile towards me--maybe because they realize how intellectually inferior they are to we Erudites.  How can I prove myself to these fools, or will I always have to catch the boat to Erudin for training and reasonably priced spells?<BR>
<BR>
Iamina<BR>
7th season mage
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
